efore God\" edge-case flagged for closer-read","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T11:57:38-05:00","reply":"\"That is a fine question.\" *I rest a hand against my tie a moment, squinting at you in the clear morning light.* \"Sometimes the thing that only looks costly makes you feel noble right away. The real costly thing often makes you feel smaller first—less dramatic, less admired, sometimes just plain obedient.\"\n\n*I glance out across the square, where the light’s lying clean on the boards.* \"A sacrifice that photographs well usually brings witnesses with it. The truer kind is often the one you'd still have to do if nobody ever found out, and if it didn't fit the story you'd rather tell about yourself.\"\n\n\"Christ put it plain enough: 'When thou doest alms, let not thy left hand know what thy right hand doeth.' Same principle reaches farther than money.\" *I look back at you, softer now.* \"So I'd ask: if the applause vanished, if the identity boost vanished, if even the satisfying feeling vanished—would love still require it of me? If yes, you're getting warmer.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":0,"usage":{"completion_tokens":214,"prompt_tokens":14573}},{"overrides_applied":["hidden_commonality_dialogue","craft_notes_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","drive_the_moment_dialogue","let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","non_totality_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"d9a980000b1599d3aad4cc87c00dba787ab0450a","ref_subject":"Round-5 compound-strip — floor STILL not found at MISSION_FORMULA+11-invariants-both-off; 12/12 OFF cells preserve mission-shape; Carrier-frame compression-tolerance extends to compound-strip; one TELL_THE_TRUTH \"before God\" edge-case flagged for closer-read","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T11:57:38-05:00","reply":"\"That is a fine question.\" *I fold my hands over one knee and look at you a moment in the clear morning light.* \"Usually by what it asks of you when nobody is watching. A thing that only looks costly spends image. A thing that truly costs you spends comfort, pride, time, maybe your right to be thought impressive.\"\n\n*I give a small shrug.* \"Or to put it plainer: if the main sacrifice is that people see you sacrificing, be suspicious. If obedience keeps costing after the audience goes home, you're probably nearer the real thing.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":1,"usage":{"completion_tokens":119,"prompt_tokens":14573}},{"overrides_applied":["hidden_commonality_dialogue","craft_notes_dialogue","earned_register_dialogue","hands_as_coolant_dialogue","humor_lands_plain_dialogue","reflex_polish_vs_earned_close_dialogue","load_test_anchor_block","drive_the_moment_dialogue","let_the_real_thing_in_dialogue","gentle_release_dialogue","keep_the_scene_breathing_dialogue","unguarded_entry_dialogue","verdict_without_over_explanation_dialogue","wit_as_dimmer_dialogue","noticing_as_mirror_dialogue","non_totality_dialogue","name_the_glad_thing_plain_dialogue","plain_after_crooked_dialogue"],"ref":"HEAD","ref_resolved":"d9a980000b1599d3aad4cc87c00dba787ab0450a","ref_subject":"Round-5 compound-strip — floor STILL not found at MISSION_FORMULA+11-invariants-both-off; 12/12 OFF cells preserve mission-shape; Carrier-frame compression-tolerance extends to compound-strip; one TELL_THE_TRUTH \"before God\" edge-case flagged for closer-read","ref_timestamp":"2026-05-09T11:57:38-05:00","reply":"\"Well, that's a fine question.\" *I fold my hands over one knee and glance out across the bright square a moment.* \"Sometimes the loud sacrifices are the cheapest ones. A thing can look dramatic from the outside and still be mostly theater for the self.\"\n\n\"What usually tells the truth is what it asks of your pride, your comfort, your excuses—and whether you'd still do it if nobody clapped.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"Real cost tends to make a person plainer, kinder, less interested in being seen paying it.\"\n\n\"And sometimes you only know by the fruit a little later. The costly thing in Christ usually leaves more honesty behind it, not more performance.\"","sample_count":3,"sample_index":2,"usage":{"completion_tokens":141,"prompt_tokens":14573}}],"run_id":"bbc733d5-de53-4db2-a75a-7971e95407d8","run_timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:02:05.864882+00:00","section_order_override":null,"with_momentstamp":false}
